<br />
I'll try to make this as simple as possible. Obviously further commenting will have to take place as the topic progresses.
<br />

<br />
#1  Simply because it allows people to play the game in a variety of ways yet achieve similar goals. That is the ONE reason. Let's face it all people play a game to "win" or to get really "good" at it. However, this game is a virtual fantasy world. Its rules are not locked in stone like say a card game. Why in the world should it not be possible to arrive at the same successes in a virtual world through alternative means when it can be done in real life as well? My understanding is that people all agree that MMORPG's should be like a fantasy life that is "somewhat" similiar to leading a real life (in terms of socio/economic status, power, experience, age, etc.... and so on). Are you telling me that the only way to acquire top economic status, power, fame, etc... in real life is through one method and one method only? Thats just ludicrous and I hope everyone reading this can see immediately how false that idea would be. EVEN if that were possibly true (and it is no where close to the realm of truth) it would still be flawed thinking because the game is supposed to make these things come to fruition for people *more* easily than real life. THAT is why we play the fantasy game in the first place and are drawn to it. 
<br />

<br />

<br />
#2 Ok frankly I don't understand your question. When I say similar gear I mean similar. This would mean that through a variety of other means people could gain the same/similar power in terms of economic game status and items that raiders do. Keep in mind that no one is arguing that encounters be done by 1 person necessarily. In fact i'm not even necessarily promoting that 4 or 5 people can do it. Althought I wont discredit that possibility could exist and be challenging as hell. However more likely i'm talking about things similar to raiding but that are much more small in scale. 5, 10, 15 people tops. This is an understandable number of people to cooperate with for encounters. 50, 60, 70+ people has gotten ridiculous and burdensome for so many people. Why should it not be possible to gather up 5 or 10 friends and do some cool shit rather than having to have some group of "guild leaders" that half of the guild really has no contact with decided when and what you and your friends are going to do? Once again, if thats your bag then go do it by all means. BUT there should be other possibilites as well.
<br />

<br />
 
<br />
#3 Ah this I really don't care much about at all. Zones access is not what bothers me one bit. Although it does basically suck beyond belief to open zones like poe, pofire, etc... that have amazing xp to raiders and there is no xp alternative of equivalency to people that dont raid heavily. Now what *does* bother me is that in a fantasy game of epic proportion where people expect to maybe play out their favorite Tolkien hero in all its glory (and power) cannot do so unless they wish to join raiding forces of enormous and unwieldy size. They cannot do this because roleplaying won't cut it. The commercials on TV and on the box say battle epic dragons, fight epic monsters, find riches beyond your dreams, and ancient artifacts of enormous power, etc....  When I started playing EQ a couple of years ago I had full intention to do these things but had no idea it meant being locked into a certain playstyle. I have overcome those things and decided to begin raiding long ago but it was much to my discomfort. This was not how I saw the game being played. I am simply arguing this for the people that cannot raid or dont want to raid.
<br />

<br />
#4 I might have missed a post somewhere in this thread so I cannot answer this question properly as I dont really know what you mean. I assume the arguments elsewhere in this thread have advocated making raid only zones that have no group content? This does maybe go back to my little piece on the wrongs of allowing insane group xp content to people that are raiding at top tier zones that others do not have access to. In any case I need more information about your question to answer it.
<br />

<br />

