Why is it that guilds must exist to raid? Lets say you keep all the 50 and 60 person raids and nothing changes. Why do they all have to be done with a guild? Sure alliances exist but they have parent guilds and community guilds that are their leadership. The answer to the question is because of the sheer number of people required to organize the encounter. It's unwieldy and unconventional if you dont have a central repository of people at disposal who all agree on a common denominator. If people want to do all that then fine. But why in the world can things not be scaled down to ALSO allow smaller communities of friends to take down impressive creatures and acquire access to zones, items, and you name it? And NOT stuff that is 1 or 2 years old either.
