That is my whole basis... where does it stop... why should the alternative be made for the 10,15,20 group and not the soloer?  If someone solos and nothing but solos and never been in a group once or guild why shouldn't they get similar rewards through soloing.  If i solo all the time you saying i would have to "sell my soul" to the 9, 14, 19 other people thats the same as you put it by people leaving smaller guilds to "sell their souls" the the raiding guilds.  
<br />

<br />
I see how you are trying to help one particular group just as i am.  I am trying to help the high standards i set for my self where you are helping those that have little to no intrest to be in large guild but are either very sociable or are in a "casual" style guild.  Im a very big picture fan i hate just looking at one aspect of a solution.  If this change people propose happens didn't you guys become selfish and leave the solo gamer out?
<br />

<br />
Now you are being misleading.  You state that Real life is fair and just and that anyone can obtain riches through multiple paths.  However, if that was true everyone would be rich but in RL we know that to be untrue.  What is true is that we have a lot of levels of economic status.  You have the billionaires, the millionaires, the people making half mills, quarter mills, the 6digit income, the 5digit income all the way down to the bum sitting on a bench asking for money.  There are very few billionaires, a little more millionaires and so forth.  What you are proposing is that the bum as just as many paths to become rich, in a perfect world you are correct.  However, the odds of a bum becoming a billionair is 99% impossible in the ways he earns money now.  What he COULD do is "sell his soul" to a company work for minimum wage get promotion after promotion till he becomes high payed employee.
<br />

<br />
See just like RW, EQ is the same.  A soloer would have to joina group of people to get more items, pp, etc and once there has to join a bigger group of people to get even more.  Its an on going chain and it works for both RL and EQ.  
<br />

<br />
As to my second question  llon hit my problem.  Take my gear:
<br />

<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=835331" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=835331</a>
<br />

<br />
By what you are saying you think its good to have alternative means to obtain all those things but with different names?  That leads to what was said why would anyone raid?  I love raiding but if i could get all that on my own would i want to raid?  No, because the incentive is gone i can group with people when ever i want just like in a raid.  I dont need a guild to group with people and get the joy of companionship and banding together to achieve glory.  The incentive is gear plan and simple thats why you raid.  On the other side though that has nothing to do with guilds...I could join a raiding guild and not raid if i want the glory, banding together stuff.
<br />

<br />
Question 4...yeah kind phrased wrong what i meant to ask was: Why would a zone with raid targets in them be allowed to people not going for those targets.  I would be more then willing to support your idea if all you want is a zone filled with 1group names and trash from EP's.  Thats why i asked question 3.  If you just the xp, TS, and one group name loots then hell i agree, by all means if you what that i would support making adjustment to current zones in which they make a PoFB and put all the mobs PoF has right now just no events or names that are considered raid targets.  That way you guys would have a path for PoFB but not be able to zone into the current one.  But if you are asking for methods to get to PoF has is then its dumb what if i go through a 6 player or 12 player path learn the techniques to beat it then show everyone i know so 54 people know about it...what happens then is those 54 people that got in 12, by 12, by 12, by 12, by 12 now can band forces and take down raid mobs.  The problem is that whole greed thing.  You think once people get a taste of EP they will just stay that way? No they will band together and take down raid mobs which they could of done if they just started as a guild.  But greed leads them that way, its bound to happen.
<br />

<br />
That relay example i gave isn't fairly analyzed by you.  That solo runner has 2 gold medals now not one.  Those 4 others have 1 because they didn't do the solo relay.  Or even if they did the MOST that could happen is one person gets 2 gold, one person gets a gold and a silver, other person gets a bronze and a gold, and that last person well is stuck with just one medal.  Are all those athletes equally compared to the standards of the olympics?  No, obviously the 2 gold medal person has his skills more tuned and on that particular day is doing better then the rest.  By following you logic Michael Phelps or whatever should give all his medals to any USA person that couldn't get one.  Why should he?  Going back to my many levels of economic status who do you think gets the most deals and has a higher image?  Michael Phelps probably does, then probably the twin gymnasts...see you point about them being equal is misleading sure if everyone won a gold in each of the event they are equal but let someone get 2 golds and then that person is more popular.
<br />

<br />
Your wrong they dont GIVE new players the idea of it the PLAYER takes their on interpretation of what the box is saying.  A box saying battle epic dragons, fight epic monsters, find riches beyond your dreams, and ancient artifacts of enormous power, etc...What do you want them to be?  100% accurate?  X amount of zones require 30people, to get X zone you have to fight mobs WY with 20 people?  Now that is ridiculous.  When i read that im thinking epic dragons eh? im pretty sure thats going to take a good force.  When i see dragon im seeing fire breath which would kill one man instantly and burns a couple more with its wide range i dont see this as the movie Shrek and an Ogre and a donkie some how gets the better of a dragon....
