                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was going to comment on what Aaeron posted but it wasn’t a lot but since I got more to work with im thinking why not.
<br />

<br />
First to Aaeron:
<br />

<br />
You missed interpreted my billionaire and millionaire thing.  I was pointing out in RL and just as EQ only so many can achieve it.  There are infinite amount of spots for both classes but only so many have done it.  Everyone COULD be a millionaire, why are they not?  Because they don’t have the skills, know how, connections, benefits, etc… Your next point is very true this is a game and there should be a lot more ways and easier ways to achieve that status.  Here's a shocker, it already is.  You guys just don’t want to look at it like that.  For example I am pretty high on the gear thing.  However, I’m poor, I have just enough AA’s to get through the difficult ones, my tradeskills are somewhat mediocre, and my schedule is strict.  Hard to believe is it?  I don’t have time to do TS, camp cash mobs, or do the xp grind.  Someone that has all 250 in TS is better then me in that term, someone with more AA’s has more time to grind or casually group, and someone that gots millions of pp is rich.  So to me a person with all TS maxed is more “powerful and rich” then me, some one with tons of pp is more “powerful and rich” and someone with more AA’s is more “powerful and rich”.  Basically your saying it would be fair for me to go to SoE and say hey raiders should get the same amount of xp as what casually players get on raids, or that by getting “flags” it should raise my TS’s.  I may have the most ways to get all that but my schedule is more strict.  I go to work come home raid for 5 hours and go to bed.  Even on light days where I just raid for 3 hours I go out and do the RL thing.  A casual gamer has the benefit of fitting they time in anyway they want.  
<br />

<br />
That leads me to Gnals part… Iue didn’t miss that in his post you should re-read it.  He clearly says that being in a constant raiding guild means he loses the xp grind.  He said he gets to do the grind once every 1-4 week.  To compensate for the lack of xp on raids I THINK its fair to give raiders other zones with higher xp/time ratio.  In a 5-hour group I could probably get 7-8AA’s so he is probably getting 12AA’s every 4 weeks.  In a constant grind a person could make that in 3 days tops.
<br />

<br />
Back to Aaeron…so competition is what this is about?  Your right greed does seem to play a lot.  I find it kind of unsettling that’s what you think is the goal.  I don’t compare my self with EP people and I don’t think other raiders do that either.  The people I compare my self with are people in the same tier as me.  I raid with my old guild every chance I get.  They are not doing EP anytime soon they are in velious and luclin.  They also do a little bit of PoP like paffa, PoN stuff, PoInnov things, not once did I compare my self with them.  They are completely different from me and their gear speaks volumes for their skill and commitment.  Someone getting an epic for them is a big deal…to my current guild they go wtf did you go through that quest.   I think it should be the same for you guys…if you belong in a guild doing EP you shouldn’t be comparing your self with high GoD guilds, the two are not the same.  I don’t compare my self with bill gates, or a CEO of a company, or a manager.  This game doesn’t absolutely require you to join an uber guild to get max challenge or enjoyment.  It MAY require those guilds for content.  I already made my point on competition, if that’s what you play the game for then clearly more sacrifices are needed.  
<br />

<br />
Your right that is the argument you guys have a lot of zones to get geared up, by your attitude your saying those zones are to good for you and not for raiders.  Most high end guilds had to do those zones why should they let you pick up EQ platinum and go level to 46 then be a PoP junkie and expect that PoP, LdoN, and GoD is where you get your gear?  Most guilds had to do the velious suck zones with suck gear, which was my point everyone works at different speeds.  In a year someone that isn’t in EP might be where I am now, instead of trying to get there as fast as you can why not do it as is however long it takes?
<br />

<br />
Gnarl the two points you made are kind of little in the big scope of things.  Uber guilds do complain about flagging and gearing apps, however that is the price we pay.  That is our difficult and for me I accept it.  When we do backflagging its not how generic as you put it.  Think of the applicant as a signer on a contract.  For a guild to flag a new app it’s expected that they will join the guild for the long run.  Your right they get a free ride through that but your missing some key things, one is that most of the time in PoP if you being backflagged for time you might end up not getting EP.  Two, after they are at the same flagging point as the rest they are earning their keep and everything after that they did earn.  Its like what most people do now, im sure most casual people here skipped velious and luclin and jumped into PoP running.  That’s perfectly fine to me but once you start complaining that you have no content or gear, that’s when the problem arises.  We have 2 chanters that don’t have time or EP gear they got GoD and stuff but key things like clicky slow they don’t.  That’s their price to pay for skipping PoP.  
<br />

<br />
Now you are taking one side and if an alternative method was made a casual gamer could PL some people wearing far beyond what was available to them.  It works the same way and there is really no way to limit the same thing you guys would do that raiders currently have to.
<br />

<br />
I’ll say this again, I would have no problem putting a mirror copy of a zone to the casually gamer but having anything that is considered raid targets omitted.  You guys would have the one group nameable and trash mobs but any events or mobs requiring more then a group or two omitted.  That way raider will get their zone and casual gamers could do a flagging process for the mirror zone.    
<br />

<br />
Also the TS argument you brought in is flimsy.  Aid Grimmel is a QUEST not a TS, yes in order to do the quest you have to have TS but its still a quest same as the 8th prayer shawl.  Even in 8th shawl the final thing requires a raid force, well when it came out anyways.      
<br />
   
<br />
Again the argument has become too wide.  You all are arguing for different reasons, you cant make an argument and for your support supply all reasons such as, competition, time restraint, gear, TS, xp, droppable loot for pp, etc…  If you guys all have different reasons it’s unfair for SoE to settle everyone’s problem.  Face it you cant satisfy everyone so now out of you majority pick the major topic and make the argument for it…you guys have to make sacrifices its either you want the xp, gear, zones, TS items, pp items.  You can not have all of them just as raiders cant having everything they could argue for.
<br />

<br />
-----Shalow on Vazaelle-------
<br />
